Namespaces</h1><h1 style="margin-top: 0px;"><p style="font-size: 11px; font-weight: 400;">Any namespace will order its components in a sequence that is meaningful for production or execution. Production begins at the leaf and rolls up to the root. Process execution is the other way round (here delivery). System implementation becomes confused and inefficient when projection seeks to serve two masters. Here the address is an upside down instruction set. By analogy, capitalist control systems project an address (the owner) onto production (the namespace).</p></h1>" vertex="1"> <mxGeometry height="110" width="680" x="40" y="560" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> </root> </mxGraphModel> </diagram> </mxfile>

h1.p: Any namespace will order its components in a sequence that is meaningful for production or execution. Production begins at the leaf and rolls up to the root. Process execution is the other way round (here delivery). System implementation becomes confused and inefficient when projection seeks to serve two masters. Here the address is an upside down instruction set. By analogy, capitalist control systems project an address (the owner) onto production (the namespace).
